animal.description:
Hi, my name is Havoc.  I am approximately 1 ½ years old.  I may be a Staffordshire Terrier/Bassett Hound Mix. My people say I have the cutest curling tail and I kind of have a bassett hound walk…my hips swish when I walk. My people say I am a hot mess…whatever that means.  I am a total busy body but in a good way.  I am not a shy girl and I have never met a stranger.  If you are looking for someone to accompany you to work, I just might be your girl.  I was found wandering around a neighborhood with my best friend Boomer and there was no family in sight.  I have had puppies in the past but thank goodness those days are behind me. A nice lady took us in and could not understand how someone could throw such a pups.  She told us not to worry, better days were ahead and made a promise to find us a new extra special family.

I am now looking for a new forever home.  I am looking forward to having a nice comfy bed to sleep in and I will need an abundance of toys and LOTS of treats!  After all…I deserve it!  I am super sweet, smart and energetic.   I love to go on neighborhood walks and just be out and about.  If you want to relax, you should know I love to cuddle and have big dreams of being a lap dog.  I am friendly with new people and I do well with other dogs.    I have never been cat tested, so my new people are going to say no homes with furry felines.    

I am house trained, crate trained, spayed, microchipped, up to date on vaccines and healthy.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Beckham came to us via our rescue partners in Northern AZ. He was rescued and living in a temporary foster home before being transported to Paw Placement.

He was named by his previous foster family and we can only guess they chose this name due to his athleticism and endurance! This boy is very much a border collie - always on the go, wanting to play with the other dogs, chase a toy, and race around the yard - and he's working on learning to just chill out in his current foster home. He's currently lying on the rug, chewing an antler, having tired out every other dog playmate in the home long ago! Beckham is still very much a puppy in that he is active and hyper and a ball of energy. He is smart and eager to please, affectionate and aggressively snuggly, sweet and silly.

Beckham most certainly needs a home with an equally active doggie playmate, or perhaps a very active owner, and one that understands/has experience with the drive of a working/herding breed. Beckham is not a dog for a first time dog owner, nor will he do well in a lazy household. Beckham loves to bike, run and hike, and he's great on a leash! Beckham is not appropriate for an apartment setting; he requires a house with a yard. He's a great medium size, and his hair is a mixture of soft, supple border collie and coarse husky - and he sheds similarly. He is crate and house trained in his foster home.

If you are interested in adopting, please complete an adoption application. Because we expect a large number of applications, and are still understaffed due to COVID19, we will only be able to email those applicants that are approved to schedule a meet and greet. Thank you in advance for your understanding if you don't hear back from us regarding your application.

animal.description:
Harrison is a handsome 5 year old Pittie mix with a huge heart to match his adorable big head. Harrison (or "Harry") gets along well with other large dogs but we feel a home with small animals is not a great fit for him due to a high prey drive. Harry loves to go for walks with you and cuddle on the couch all day. His favorite place to be is on a pile of soft pillows, blankies, you name it - he's snuggling on it. We think his "beefy" exterior is balanced by his soft, tender heart. Harrison is house trained and has been in a foster home for around five months while we worked on diagnosing chronic skin and GI issues. We have learned that Harry needs to be on a hypoallergenic food and has also benefitted from medication to control chronic skin allergies. Harry also prefers to be near his people and while he has been safe left home alone, he does vocalize at first, so apartment life might be not be for him. We would love to talk with you about Harrison and tell you more about his medical information and why he might make a great addition to your family! 

Since Harrison is in foster care, we ask that you please submit an adoption questionnaire via our website if you would like to meet him!

Bullwinkle is a bouncy, energetic, muscular, and playful, nine-year-old, 65-pound, brindle and white, male Am Staff Terrier looking for a loving guardian.
 
Someone cropped Bullwinkle’s ears to make him look tough, but he is a happy-go-lucky guy who loves to have his belly rubbed. He is a strong and solid dog who loves to play ball. He is full of tail wags for everyone he meets. 

He knows the commands sit and down. He rides well in the car; he just curls up in the passenger seat. He’s great on leashed walks as well. 

He is housebroken and crate-trained. Bullwinkle is de-wormed, neutered, up-to-date on vaccines, micro-chipped, heartworm-tested and on monthly preventative. His adoption fee of $200 benefits the rescued dogs of Lucky Dog Rescue. 

I first photographed this guy back in January of 2013 and he has been kenneled waiting for a loving home for over seven years! Isn’t it time someone took a chance on him? He's looking for a home as the one and only pet.

To meet and possibly adopt him, please contact Melia at melia88@comcast.net or 708-224-1900. 

He is currently being kenneled in Union, Illinois.

animal.description:
Please contact Jo Ellen (hwbdogrescue@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Callie is a beautiful 2-year-old Great Dane. She was suffering from extreme neglect and malnourishment when she was rescued near the Texas/Mexico border. Her former owner cruelly housed Callie on a dirt lot and her only shelter from extreme Texas weather was a three-sided plywood box. Callie was tethered to a tall metal pole and she could only walk in endless circles around that pole. During violent thunder storms, Callie frequently faced death by electrocution from lightning strikes. She often was forced to drink dirty water from a 5-gallon bucket coated with slime. During the Texas summers where temperatures can exceed 100 degrees, Callie was at daily risk for heat stroke. In the winter months, Callie's malnourished body would shiver as she laid on the cold and damp dirt.
Despite her heartbreaking history, Callie thrived in her new foster home where she shown kindness for the first time in her life. She loves human companionship and interacts nicely with the other dogs in her foster home. Not surprisingly, Callie is a little needy and wants nothing more than to be near a human. Accordingly, she will need to be kenneled when left alone at home.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)

You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.

Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.

Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.

Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and adults dogs are tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ 1/30/21 8:39 PM

animal.description:
Bailey is a sweet and fun-loving shar pei mix of about 2 1/2 years old that hopes to get scooped up real soon. Bailey isn't used to being away from home but sadly, he is with us because he just didn't get along with the other dog in his home. Bailey appears to be ok with some female dogs, but he'll need a home with no male dogs, cats, or young kids. He's a nervous guy that takes a little bit to trust new people but once he does, he is your very best friend. Bailey is an absolute love when he gets to know you. He's well-behaved, housebroken, listens well, he's curious and outgoing, and he's an expert fetcher. He warms up much quicker to women than to men, but in a patient and loving home, he'll be everyone's best buddy. He just needs a chance. File#29754 9/3/20 Call 609-693-1900 or email: office@ahsppz.org for an appointment to meet Bailey.

If interested please visit our Forked River Shelter. We are open Mon. - Fri. from 12:00 P. M. - 6:00 P. M.; and Sat. & Sun. 12:00 P. M. - 5:00 P. M. for directions call 609-693-1900. There is an adoption donation required. The society cannot accept personal checks but we do accept Visa, MC, AE, Discover and cash. As part of our adoption process, we must have proof of residency. Homeowners must show proof of ownership; landlord approval is required for renters before an adoption can be approved.And as always we thank you for your kindness in opening your heart & home to a Society orphan.

animal.description:
Brandy was picked up as a stray when she was very young, and it became obvious right away that this pretty girl had a rough start. Whatever she has gone through, it has made her scared of everything. She is an example of a dog that should not be in a shelter. She really needs a loving a home where she can feel safe and loved. At this time she is scare of her shadow and we need to find her a home, a patient, quiet home where she can start to feel comfortable in her own skin. 

Brandy is good around other dogs but we would not recommend her for a busy, active home with lots of people or children. She really needs a patient home where she can feel loved and comfortable and become more socialized to new people and places.

 If you have a big heart for helping those who really need the time and attention, meeting this girl may be right up your alley.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

animal.description:
Hi! My name is KFC and I am a 7-year-old Shephard/Chow mix! I am an easy-going, fun-loving girl! I am currently in a foster home and not at HSNBA, so if you are interested in meeting me, please contact the nice folks at HSNBA so they can put you in contact with my foster family to set up a meet & greet! You can e-mail HSNBA at adoption@hsnba.org, call us at: (830) 629-5287 or stop by HSNBA at 3353 Morningside Dr. to get your information sent over to my foster home. My foster family is the best and can give you more information on me.
Just so you know, I have tested heartworm positive. This means I have a parasite and need treatment. While my friends at HSNBA desperately want to help me, the shelter is too stressful an environment to undertake treatment and treatment itself is very expensive. The shelter has a few options to help with treatment, and if I steal your heart you should talk with them and your vet about what my treatment is like. For more information on heartworms, please visit the American Heartworm Society here https://www.heartwormsociety.org/pet-owner-resources/heartworm-basics

Can't wait to find my furever family!HSNBA lists all animals online from the moment of intake, and our listings are updated automatically every midnight. Some of these animals may not be available for adoption at this moment, but you can always call the shelter at 830-629-5287 for clarification on the adoption process or the animal's current status.

animal.description:
*** Lioness is available for adoption in our Foster to Adopt Program ***

Hey, my name is Lioness and I love to snuggle with my humans! If I see you sitting alone you bet that I am gonna come and snuggle into you until you start to pet me! I also LOVE to sleep next to my people! It is one of my favorite things to do! 

When it comes to other dogs, I do fine, just give me some time to get used to them and we'll be best of friends. When I get used to my new friends I LOVE playing with them. However, I would much rather be with my people! They are my top priority! 

Hope to meet you soon!

FOSTER TO ADOPT:
Lioness just completed Heartworm treatment and is waiting for a negative test result which can take 2-9 months after treatment. During these months, she will need to make sure her heart rate is not elevated due to high energy play or exercise. Lioness is only available through the Foster to Adopt Program at this time. The committment will be for an adoption but will be fostering until she is cleared with a negative Heartworm test result. All of the medical expenses will be paid for by the rescue while she is in a foster to adopt home. Food, kennel, grooming and other supplies will be provided by the foster in the foster to adopt program. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------


All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $450

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

HI, I AM TRUDY. I COULD BE THE BEST PRESENT YOU WILL EVER GET AND YOU COULD BE THE BEST PRESENT I WILL EVER GET BY GIVING ME A PERMANENT FOREVER HOME. I AM 1/2 TO 3/4 GERMAN SHEPHERD AND 8 MONTHS OLD. I HAVE HAD ALL MY SHOTS AND FIXED AND READY TO GO FOR YOU. MY FOSTER PARENTS LOVE ME AND I HAVE SPECIAL NEEDS. WHEN I WAS LITTLE SOMEONE WAS NOT GOOD TO ME AND I AM BLIND IN ONE EYE. SO I AM A SPECIAL NEEDS DOG, YOU HAVE TO BE PATIENT WITH ME. I NEED A WELL FENCED YARD AND LOTS OF LOVE AND ATTENTION. I LOVE EVERYONE AND EVERYBODY. GIVE ME A GOOD HOME AND I WILL BE YOUR BEST FRIEND. THANKS. TRUDY

Trudy is a special pup. She is very friendly and loving and she likes for you to sit down so she can crawl in your lap. She wants to play with her foster siblings but they aren't really interested. We don't know Trudy's background, but she has some slight physical limitations. She can be walked on a harness but not with a collar. She is sensitive to anesthesia and she is blind in one eye so may startle easy when approached from that side. Other than that, Trudy is just a loving pup who needs a furever home.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Marshall County Humane Society is now following CDC guidelines for Covid-19 in order to keep everyone as safe as possible. We are showing dogs and cats to prospective adopters, but only on the grounds outside our shelter. We will need appointment to show the animal and we will want to have social distancing of 6' while you are there and we are wearing masks. We are doing Zoom interviews to see inside of your home since we aren't going into homes for home visit. We do come to your home before finalizing adoption to check the security of your fence if you are adopting a dog. Our dogs are given much care and attention and we treat every medical need of animal once we take them in.
MCHS is a limited intake adoption center. We are an all volunteer, non-profit organization. All of our animals are disease free, have been spayed/neutered and are up to date on shots. We charge a Dog adoption fee of $125 which includes a microchip. Our Cat adoption fee is $75.00. Most of our dogs will require a fenced yard. To fill out application, go to our website Marshallcountyhumanesociety.org, go to Adoption Info tab and click on Application. For more info, call 662-564-2900. I'm a young red coonhound mix who just needs a new family to love. The volunteers say that I'm calm and loveable. I do get a little nervous around small kids so best family for me would have older kids or adults. Come and see me soon by calling 662-564-2900 or E-mail DogsNCats11@gmail.com to make an appointment to meet me.
All our animals have been spayed or neutered and up to date on all preventives and shots and we are microchipped. Dog adoption fee is $125.
Fill out application at Marshallcountyhumanesociety.org and go to Adoption Info Tab.

animal.description:
Meet Karma!  She's an adult Pit Bull type girl, brought to us by Law Enforcement when her owner was arrested.  No one came for her, and Karma is in need of a new home.  Karma was quite distraught by her new housing situation, and it took some time for her to allow us to handle her.  She's slowly coming out of her shell, and while she is leery of strangers, she is showing us how playful she is!  Karma loves her walks, loves to play fetch, and is obsessed with our big jolly ball!  Any potential adopters for this pretty girl should be prepared to put in some time and allow her to get used to them before they make a commitment.  Although she seems to always be on guard, she would likely relax and show her wonderful self in a loving home environment.  She has been pretty non-reactive to most of our other dogs. animal.description:
Meet Charlie!  He's a large Yellow Lab type of guy, about 4 years old.  He's free spirited and independent.  Charlie's favorite things seem to be playing fetch & the water!  He was actually found at the river, and although he is micro-chipped, his owner did not come for him.  Charlie gets so excited for fetch, he doesn't notice the hand holding the ball, so would likely do best in a home with no small children.  Charlie is blind in his right eye, which may affect his depth perception.  Although he will sit, he doesn't seem to have had much training or discipline, so would do best with an experienced owner.  He's a high energy guy, and "catch me if you can" also seems to be a favorite game of his.  He needs a home where he can be kept secure.  He doesn't care for our other dogs, so may do best as your only buddy.  Charlie just loves being a dog.  He doesn't seem to care too much about affection, he just wants to run and have fun!  Charlie was adopted, but returned after an incident with a cat, he needs a home with no kitties.  His humans will also need to be mindful when Charlie meets new people, apparently he can be selective about who he trusts.  If you're looking for a big buddy who is always ready for fun, come out and meet Charlie! 
 Come check out Charlie and our other dogs available for adoption at 2650 Washington Blvd, Crescent City, CA 95531.

Please call us at (707) 464-7235 for additional information.  More photos of this dog may be available on the Dogs of Del Norte County Facebook page.

animal.description:
**Due to breed restrictions, I cannot be adopted out to a home in  Commerce City, Louisville, or Lone Tree**

How's it goin'? My name is Dumplin', and I'm a 4 year old, mixed breed, bundle of joy! I was brought into MaxFund as a stray dog and I've been here, chillin', ever since!

When I first came in, I was really confused and somewhat afraid, so I wasn't getting along with other dogs at all and I was very picky about the people I wanted to be with. Since my arrival, I've done some training with MaxFund humans to relax a bit and become more comfortable. I've really grown into my personality, and I am a fan favorite here! I'm super sweet and cuddly, but also energetic and I love to play whenever I can.

I am a big girl, weighing in around 60lbs, and I don't quite know that I'm that big. I move my muscular body around all the time (for fun of course) but for this reason, I wouldn't be able to go to a home with kiddos under 10 years. I would also prefer to be the only animal in the home. I'm still not a huge fan of other dogs and people tell me I'd probably chase cats around. I just want all the dang attention!

If my cute photos haven't done enough, come on down to the dog shelter and let my smile charm you in person! Please call the dog shelter at 303.595.4917 to make an appointment. Just ask for Dumplin'!!


MaxFund is a physical shelter located at 1005 Galapago St in Denver, Colorado.
If you are interested in learning more about a dog, please call 303-595-4917
Due to Covid we are showing dogs by appointment only.

This PetFinder account is managed by volunteers, and the most up-to-date information is at the shelter.
How our adoption process works:
1. You MUST come into the shelter to meet a dog you are interested in (and meet a few others, while you’re at it!)
               
                Our hours are 10-5 Mon, Wed, Thu Fri / 11-5 Saturday / 12-5 Sunday

                We suggest you call ahead to be sure the dog(s) do not have pending applications
2. You will fill out your adoption application, including references, after finding a dog you’d like to adopt
3. The application review and reference checks will take up to 3-5 business days; you will not be able to bring a dog home same-day
                We only take 2 applications per dog, before they are unavailable. This is why we suggest you call ahead to check the status of the pup!
 
We do not adopt out-of-state.
Thank you for choosing to rescue!

animal.description:
Raven weighs 72lbs, but she's on the skinny side and probably needs at least 5 - 10 more. We believe she is a Cane Corso mix, with something smaller (perhaps Boxer?). She has natural ears and a docked tail, which she loves to wag wag waggle at you! She adores all people and is incredibly tolerant of being loved on (as you can see!). She likes to explore and investigate, followed up by some serious naps, hah. Raven is very very good with dogs that are about medium sized or bigger. She loves Poe Poe, our American Bully, who is about 50lbs. I would not place her with cats or dogs that are much smaller than Poe, as she does have some serious prey drive and likes to chase smaller animals.

Raven is house trained and crate trained, but she really doesn't need to be crated as she's completely non-destructive. No food aggression or resource guarding issues; apart from her prey drive, she is super laid back and go with the flow. She does have pretty bad arthritis, so she's no hiking buddy, but I think she'd love some gentle daily walks so she can see the sights. She is about 10 - 11 years old, which is pretty on up there for a Mastiff-type breed, but she's still got life left and items to check off her bucket list!

If you think you could be the perfect home for Raven, please visit OldDogHomeGA.com to fill out an application! We will continue maintaining her veterinary care until she is more stable, but she could go home on a foster-to-adopt at any time.

Ronnie is finally ready for his forever home! He recently had hip surgery and is all healed up and moving around perfectly! Ronnie is a special boy that is playful with people and with other dogs, but is food aggressive and has bitten in these circumstances and out of fear Ronnie also gets too excited when playing so can be nippy with ankles when playing, so he needs to be in an adult only home and given lots of structure and boundaries.
